The paper discusses the use of deep reinforcement learning in designing intelligent systems, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions multi-agent learning and human-machine interactions, which are relevant to robotics (cs.RO) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper proposes a software architecture for designing deep RL-based systems, which is relevant to software engineering (cs.SE) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
